# DevOps CI/CD Project

## GitHub → Jenkins → Docker → AWS ECR → AWS EKS → ArgoCD

This project demonstrates a **complete real-world DevOps CI/CD pipeline** used in modern cloud environments.
It automates the process of **building, packaging, storing, and deploying an application to Kubernetes** using GitOps principles.

The pipeline integrates multiple DevOps tools to create a fully automated deployment workflow.

---

# Project Architecture

```
Developer
   │
   ▼
GitHub (Application Code)
   │
   ▼
Jenkins Pipeline
   │
   ├── Build Docker Image
   ├── Push Image to AWS ECR
   │
   ▼
Update Kubernetes Manifest in Git
   │
   ▼
ArgoCD detects change
   │
   ▼
Deploy to EKS Cluster
```

---

# Tools Used

| Stage              | Tool    | Purpose                            |
| ------------------ | ------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Source Code        | GitHub  | Store application code             |
| CI Pipeline        | Jenkins | Automate build process             |
| Containerization   | Docker  | Package application                |
| Container Registry | AWS ECR | Store Docker images                |
| Orchestration      | AWS EKS | Run containers                     |
| Deployment         | ArgoCD  | GitOps-based Kubernetes deployment |

